His great work of the Sentences is looked on as the source of the Scholastic Theology of the Latin Church, as that of Damascenus had been of the Greek. Of the occasion and nature of this work, of so much importance in the conduct of Papal Theology, Du Pin has given a full and interesting account in his Ec- clesiastical History, Cent. 12. Chap. xv.
